data.meta_description: Shonda Gloude-Jones was born in Washington, DC in 1978 and was an accomplished basketball player.  an army veteran, she told me about her childhood, her service,  The interview includes discussion of joining the Army, personal struggles and achievements throughout her life, her mother's influence and inspiration, challenges of being a woman in the military, being injured, the Wounded Warrior Project, earning her associates degree, and her family as an important support system.
